44
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:17,360
Right.

45
00:02:17,659 --> 00:02:18,479
Hi, it's nice to meet you.

46
00:02:18,580 --> 00:02:20,039
Oh, it's nice to meet you too.

47
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,280
Right, exactly.

48
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:28,840
So she went on this girl, Michelle, to ask if he is visiting Shanghai for business or pleasure.

49
00:02:29,460 --> 00:02:33,939
All right, this is an important difference, something that we often talk about in small talk.

50
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:35,960
You can travel for business.

51
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:41,659
That means business trips where you can travel to see different sites and have fun.

52
00:02:41,659 --> 00:02:45,560
That's called pleasure, and so we often hear this phrase, business or pleasure.

53
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:50,639
Right, so if someone comes to your country, you say, oh, so are you here for business or pleasure?

54
00:02:50,639 --> 00:02:54,400
Oh, I'm here on business, or I'm here to see the sights.

55
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,840
Okay, very good.

56
00:02:56,740 --> 00:03:01,080
And so James is actually in Shanghai doing both things.

57
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:09,460
He's on a business trip, but he's also taking Mandarin classes, and so Michelle went on to say, that's great, how's it going?

58
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:12,340
All right, you're going to hear this all the time in English.

59
00:03:12,419 --> 00:03:15,879
We say how's it going to our friends and family.

60
00:03:16,399 --> 00:03:25,680
I wouldn't say it in a formal occasion with my boss or with my teacher, but it's very casual, very informal, and it's a way to ask how things are.

61
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:29,039
So you're taking classes, how's it going?

62
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,280
Exactly.

63
00:03:30,819 --> 00:03:33,759
So this basically means how are the classes going?

64
00:03:33,939 --> 00:03:35,020
How is everything?

65
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:38,400
Right, or you could say, oh, Marco, I haven't seen you in a while.

66
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,460
How is it going?

67
00:03:40,139 --> 00:03:43,240
And that's another way of saying hi to someone or saying, how are you?

68
00:03:43,580 --> 00:03:44,039
How are you?

69
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:45,860
How have you been recently?

70
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,900
So there are two differences in that phrase there.

71
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:51,719
In this case, Michelle is asking how the Mandarin classes are going.

72
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:52,500
How is it?

73
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:53,539
Is it good?

74
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:54,020
Is it bad?

75
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,659
Is it difficult?

76
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:56,300
Is it easy?

77
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:57,300
Et cetera.

78
00:03:57,400 --> 00:04:01,659
But if you say to someone, hi, I haven't seen you for such a long time, how's it going?

79
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:03,819
That's more of a how are you type thing.

80
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,580
That's like how's your life going.

81
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:05,979
Exactly.

82
00:04:06,099 --> 00:04:08,620
So just think about what you're talking about.

83
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,819
Are you talking about general situations, like a person's life?

84
00:04:12,289 --> 00:04:16,699
Or are you talking about maybe lessons or class or a job?

85
